CORDES LAKES, Ariz. (AP) — A Yavapai County Sheriff’s deputy has died after being shot by a suspect who now is in custody, authorities said Wednesday.They said Sgt. Richard Lopez was shot Tuesday afternoon in Cordes Lakes and airlifted to a Phoenix hospital where he later died.Sheriff’s officials said the 51-year-old Lopez was a 14-year veteran of the department.The Prescott Valley resident leaves behind a wife and two daughters.County Sheriff David Rhodes said at a late-night news conference that Lopez was pursuing a man suspected of stealing and the shooting occurred in a Cordes Lakes neighborhood.Rhodes said Lopez was found unresponsive and was airlifted to HonorHealth Deer Valley Medical Center in Phoenix where he underwent surgery before he “ultimately succumbed to his injuries.”The sheriff said the suspect was taken into custody following an hourslong barricade situation at his home and was being held on suspicion of first-degree murder at a Prescott jail.ADVERTISEMENTThe suspect’s name wasn’t immediately released.“The violence against law enforcement, we are seeing it escalate everywhere, and it has got to stop,” Rhodes said. “These are community servants, these are people that are out there serving the community, protecting Life, Liberty, liberty and property. And we, they do not deserve this.”